      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:21:3",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) لَوْ كَانَ يَنْبَغِي لِأَحَدٍ أَنْ يُرْجَمَ مَرَّتَيْنِ لَرُجِمَ اللُّوطِيُّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, from his<sup>asws</sup> forefathers<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘If it was befitting for anyone that he should be stoned twice, it would be sodomist to be stoned’."
        ]
      }
